{
  "texts": [
    "GAN presents an information-driven regularizer, it tries to improve itself and guarantees that the learned features bring the outcome close to the ground truth.",
    "In basic GAN architectures, D and G are executed as Multi-Layered Perceptrons (MLPs).",
    "U-Net is the most used architecture as the G for GAN.",
    "Another frequently used G in GANs is the ResNet, as highlighted in the work by Emami et al.",
    "ResNet stands out for its ease of optimization and its ability to reliably produce the desired results."
  ]
}